Flaky can be configured to call a function after a flaky failure. It was designed as a way to skip reruns, but it could also be used to delay them. See #55 for more details. I'd imagine you'd do something like this:

    import time

    def delay_rerun(*args):
        time.sleep(1)
        return True

    @flaky(rerun_filter=delay_rerun)
    def test_flaky_thing():
        pass

