Try this and plone.api itself in client projects and see if you can abstain yourselves from putting all business logic in templates again. I recommend highly against this, though.

Personally, I just create a helper view. Most times I need more than just and plone.api call. AFAIK in the ZMI, PFG, and most RPython tal:conditions you already have context, container, user and some more stuff.

```python
from plone import api
from Products.Five import BrowserView

class api(BrowserView):
    def __call__(self):
        return self

    @property
    def content(self):
        return api.content

    @property
    def env(self):
        return api.env

    @property
    def group(self):
        return api.group

    @property
    def portal(self):
        return api.portal

    @property
    def user(self):
        return api.user
```

```xml
<configure
    xmlns="http://namespaces.zope.org/zope"
    xmlns:browser="http://namespaces.zope.org/browser"
    i18n_domain="plone.api">

  <browser:page
      for="*"
      name="api"
      class="[dotted.name.to.view]"
      permission="zope.View"
      />

</configure>```

